  "text": "where the quantity on the left hand side enters the neutrino oscillation formulas (see below). For the distances L and neutrino energies E that match the above relation, defining what are called Short BaseLine (SBL) oscillations, the terms due to the solar and atmospheric mass splittings cannot develop, and only the effect of ∆m 2 41 must be considered. At SBL, therefore, one can write the transition probability between a neutrino or antineutrino of flavor α and one of flavor β in the following way (see e.g. [CITATION_1] ):",
